Internal bickering in the TDP came to the fore in Pulivendula constituency in Kadapa district with followers of one leader tearing away the flexies of Chief Minister N. Chandrababu Naidu and his son and party general secretary Nara Lokesh put up by another group in Vempalle town on Friday.Followers of coordinator of Rayalaseema TDP training classes Bhoomireddy Ramgopal Reddy lodged a complaint with the Vempalle police alleging that followers of Deputy Chairman of A.P. Legislative Council S.V. Satish Kumar Reddy tore the flexies put up near the Vempalle bus stand and four-road junction. Mr. Satish Reddyâ€™s followers resorted to the act alleging that Mr. Ramgopal Reddy was neglecting TDP activists.